plugins.author: Artem Popov
plugins.name: Andes
plugins.description: Andes is a software synthesiser plugin in early stages of development. The core of Andes is an original oscillator which uses a pseudo-3D version of Perlin noise to produce distinctively digital sound.

plugins.author: Pascal Gauthier
plugins.name: Dexed
plugins.description: Synthesizer closely modeled on the Yamaha DX7

plugins.author: Brain Control
plugins.name: Tunefish
plugins.description: Tunefish is a tiny virtual analogue synth that was originally developed  for the 64k intros of the demo group Brain Control.

plugins.author: Martin Eastwood
plugins.name: Mverb
plugins.description: Studio quality, open-source reverb. Its release was intended to provide a practical demonstration of Dattorro’s figure-of-eight reverb structure and provide the open source community with a high quality reverb.

plugins.author: Claes Johanson
plugins.name: Surge
plugins.description: Hybrid synthesizer featuring many synthesis techniques, a great selection of filters, a flexible modulation engine, a smorgasbord of effects, and modern features like MPE and microtuning.

plugins.author: Christian Borß
plugins.name: HybridReverb2
plugins.description: Convolution-based reverberation effect which combines the superior sound quality of a convolution reverb with the tuning capability of a feedback delay network.

plugins.author: Michael Willis
plugins.name: Dragonfly Reverb
plugins.description: Dragonfly Reverb is a bundle of free audio effect plugins for Linux, MacOS, and Windows.
